data.name: Barbecue Honey-Glazed Chicken Thighs
data.quickTastyDescription: Succulent chicken thighs marinated in a sweet and tangy honey barbecue glaze, grilled to perfection.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat your grill to medium-high heat.
In a bowl, mix together honey, barbecue sauce, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and black pepper to create the marinade.
Place the chicken thighs in a large resealable bag and pour the marinade over them. Seal the bag and toss to coat the chicken evenly. Let marinate in the fridge for at least 30 minutes.
Once marinated, remove the chicken from the bag and discard the excess marinade.
Brush the grill grates with olive oil to prevent sticking.
Place the chicken thighs on the grill, skin side down. Grill for about 5-7 minutes per side, or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (75°C) and the chicken is nicely charred.
Remove from the grill, let rest for a few minutes, then garnish with fresh parsley before serving.
